                <msContents>
                  
                    <summary>Pustaha.</summary>
                   
                    <textLang mainLang="btx">Karo-Batak</textLang>
                    
                    <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Batak_66486_1">
                        
                        <textLang mainLang="btx">Karo-Batak</textLang>
                        
                        <note>Although this MS is modern, it is a good copy of a Karo-Batak text which had originally come from the Toba-Batak village of Silalahi on the north-west coast of Lake Toba.</note>
                        <note>The subject of the MS is tambar sibérétatt késah, a medicine that may be used against various diseases, as an antidote against poison, and as a protection against inimical magic. It is unclear what the name of this medicine means (tambar medicine; késah breath; but there is no suitable explanation of sibérétan). The prescriptions for the various applications of this medicine are rather more detailed than is usual in Batak MSS.</note>
  
                    </msItem>
                </msContents>
                
